latestPosts.caption: 2024 - a year mostly spent in transit. Great wins and great losses. Also, everyone in this video is a main character and I love you guys. Let’s go ‘25, you have great shoes to fill!

Apart from being just the most beautiful boy ever, Hero was intelligent, wise and patient beyond words. He was the youngest member of our family. He brought us joy like no other. I wish I could say that he lived a full life, he went away so suddenly that I can’t be sure. What a beautiful and funny dog, he was so grateful and happy and a little puppy all the time. I could write a book compiling all the moments of joy and perspective he gave me.

What no one tells you about greiving is that you’re not just mourning the unimaginable loss of a loved one, you’re also mourning the memories, laughs and little screams of joy that were exclusive to that one being. I miss coming home to your zoomies, the little tongue out when you sleep and scratching your silly bum. Thank you for changing our lives. Hope you’re chasing and troubling little animals and running in endless fields.
